name: Homemade Mountain Dew: Baja Blast
description: 1 Part Sprite, 1 Part Blue Poweraid, 2 Parts Original Mountain Dew

name: Dr. Pepper Brownies
description: To Any Browny Mix, Add 2 Eggs, 1/2 cup of oil(veg), 1/4 cup of Dr. Pepper, chocolate chips(optional), mix and bake at 350 for 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean

name: Homemade In & Out Spread
description: 1/2 cup of mayo, 3 tbsp of ketchup, 2 tbsp of sweet pickled relish, 1/2 tsp of sugar, 1 1/2 tsp of distilled white vinegar, splach of Worcestershire sauce(optional), refrigerate for at least 1 hour after mixing

name: Olive Garden Alfrado Sauce
description: Saute 3oz of butter with 1 tbsp of garlic on medium heat for 1 minute, then add 2 tbsp of all purpose flour,1 1/2 cup of milk,1 1/2 cup of heavy cream, 1/2 cup of parmesan, 1/2 cup of romano cheese, add salk and pepper to taste, reduce to low heat and stir continuously unil done

name: KFCs 11 Herbs And Spices
description: 2/3 tsp salt, 1/2 tsp of thyme, 1/2 tsp of basil, 1/3 tsp of oregano, 1 tsp of celery salt, 1 tsp of black pepper,  1 tsp of dried mustard, 4 tsp of paprika, 2 tsp of garlic salt,  1 tsp of ground ginger, 3 tsp of white pepper

name: OG Supermarket Sugar Cookies
description: 2 1/4 cup of flower, 1/2 tsp of baking powder, 1/4 teaspoon of baking soda, 1 tbsp of cornstarch, 1/2 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 cup  of butter(Room Temp), 1 cup of sugar, 1 egg, 1/4 cup of sour cream(room temp), 1 1/2 tsp of vanilla extract, bake at 350 until you can poke a toothpick trough the center and no batter comes out

name: Homemade Cosmic Brownies
description: 1/2 cup flour, 1/4 cup cocoa powder, 1/4 tsp of salt, 3/4 cup of brown sugar, 5 tbsp of unsalted butter, 1 egg, 1 egg yolk, 1 tbsp of honey, 1 tsp of vanilla, bake at 350 until you can poke a toothpick trough the center and no batter comes out

name: Nutella Ice Cream
description: fill empty Nutella jar with heavy whipping cream, add sugar and vnilla extract to taste(it pays to be conservative here), add a pinch of salt, add toppings, shake well, put in freezer for min 4 hour perferably over night

name: McDonalds Pancake Batter
description: add 1 1/3 cups of any pancake mix, 1/2 cup of water, 1/2 cup of McDonalds sprite

name: Homemade Saracha
description: get 1 3/4 lbs of red jalapeno peppers, remove stems, cut longways, in a food proccessor mix in peppers, 3 Garlic Cloves, 2 tbsp of garlic powder, 2 tbsp of sugar, 1 tbsp of LIGHT brown sugar, 1 tbsp of kosher salt, run food processor until its a coarse puree, pour mixture into a GLASS container for 1 Week and leave at room temp, mix once a day unitl the 7th day, on the 8th day pour into a saucepan and add 1/2 cup of white distilled vinegar, cook to a boil, let rest for 5 minutes, put BACK into the food processor for 3 minutes(add water if it feels too thick), strain through a fine mesh strainer and put it back in a glass container

name: Better Kraft Mac & Cheese
description: 2 Boxs Of Kraft Mac & Cheese, 3 cups of Water, 1 cup of milk, 2 tbsp of butter, Add Seasoning(Your Choice), cook on medium heat then add cheese packets, add more cheese(any) on top, let it get to a boil, simmer and stir for 8-13 minutes

name: McDonald's Sweet & Sour Sauce
description: 1/4 cup of Apricot Preserve, 1/4 cup of Peach Preserve, 2 tbsp of Corn Syrup, 5 tsp of White Vinegar, 1/2 tsp of Soy Sauce,  1/2 tsp of Mustard, 1/4 tsp of salt, 1/8 tsp of Garlic, 1 1/2 tsp of Cornstarch, simmer in a saucepan for 5 minutes with 2 tbsp of water

name: Texas Roadhouse Honey Butter
description: 1 Stick Of Salted Butter(room temp), 1 1/2 tbsp of honey, 1/4 tbsp cinnamon, 1/4 cup of powdered sugar(optional), whisk until combined and refrigerate

name: Popeye's Biscuits
description: All Puropse Flour: 2 cups, Sugar: 1 tbsp, Salt: 1 tbsp, Whole Milk: 1/4 cups, Butter Milk: 1/2 cups, Baking Powder: 1 1/2 tbsp, Baking soda: 1/2 tbsp, Cold Butter: 1/2 cups, Mix Ingredients, Put On Baking Sheet, Bake at 400 degrees(F) for 22 minutes
